  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka in the lead in the second Test",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Batting first in the two-match series, which began last Friday in Galle, Australia scored 364 in their first innings with Steve Smith's unbeaten 145 and Marnus Labuschein's 104 all out. In bowling, Test debutant Prabhat Jayasuriya took 6, Kasun Rajitha 2, Ramesh Mendis and another Test debutant Mahesh Dikshana took one wicket each.",
        "In reply, Sri Lanka batting in their first innings at the end of today's third day lost 6 wickets and scored 431 runs. Currently in the field, Dinesh Chandimal is unbeaten with 118 runs and Ramesh Mendis with seven runs. Earlier, captain Timuth Karunaratne scored 86, Kusal Mendis scored 85, Test debutant Kamindu Mendis scored 61 and Angelo Mathews scored 52. In bowling, Mitchell Starc 2, Mitchell Swabson 2, Nathan Lyon took 2 wickets."
      ],
